## Phase 5: Performance Considerations

### 5.1 Draw Call Budget

For a 20x25 grid (500 tiles), worst case:
- 500 base sprite draws (existing)
- Up to 500x6 = 3000 transition sprite draws (worst case if every tile has all 6 neighbors different)
- Realistic case: most tiles share terrain with 4-5 neighbors, so ~500-1000 active transition components

**Mitigations:**
- Transition components are set invisible when not needed (no draw call when invisible)
- All transition components share the same material (same UMaterialInterface parent), enabling UE's automatic instancing
- Paper2D sprites are lightweight quads

### 5.2 Memory Budget

- 6 `UPaperSpriteComponent` per tile = 6 x 500 = 3000 additional components. Each is a lightweight scene proxy.
- 6 `UMaterialInstanceDynamic` per tile = 3000 MIDs. Each MID is very small (just parameter overrides).
- Total additional memory: roughly 5-10 MB for a 500-tile grid. Acceptable.

### 5.3 Update Cost

- `UpdateTileTransitions` does 6 neighbor lookups (TMap::Find, O(1) amortized) and 6 material parameter updates. Very fast.
- `UpdateAllTransitions` iterates all tiles once. For 500 tiles: 3000 neighbor lookups + up to 3000 material updates. Well under 1ms.
- `UpdateTransitionsAround` touches at most 7 tiles (1 center + 6 neighbors). Negligible.

### 5.4 Optimization: Disable Tick on HexTile

The current `ALFPHexTile::Tick` is empty. Set `PrimaryActorTick.bCanEverTick = false` in the constructor to avoid per-frame overhead for 500 actors. (This is an existing optimization opportunity, not strictly part of this feature.)

